<../../../index.trig> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#8f6591f4baf4db576ad9d40466a18805>.
<#8f6591f4baf4db576ad9d40466a18805> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Create>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/0d364939-9a93-4e82-be03-c2644dd27f62/resource/bf6cdc9c-f210-4816-8c35-01f4b02c5ced>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-06-15T15:32:59.966Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#8f6591f4baf4db576ad9d40466a18805> {
<https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/0d364939-9a93-4e82-be03-c2644dd27f62/resource/bf6cdc9c-f210-4816-8c35-01f4b02c5ced> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "UVIS_paper"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Text files containing extinction (mean between 320 and 340 nm) and reff vertical profiles  for the UVIS dataset between MY 34 Ls 163° until the end of MY36. Name, latitude and local time are also provide to help reader identify the occultation in other dataset.\r\nThese profiles passed the selection criteria and without the latitudinal binning used in the different plots. Using this data the user can reproduce all the figure related to the vertical profiles."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2024-04-25T11:27:11.331750"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
