<../../../index.trig> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#10b99c8d3fd250b356f6e14aa52da615>.
<#10b99c8d3fd250b356f6e14aa52da615> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Create>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/bc9068b4-00c0-41fd-a1fa-54a3afaa14a4/resource/e8ae6e17-cdad-44d9-a6c0-a6441a1c90b9>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-06-15T15:33:01.161Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#10b99c8d3fd250b356f6e14aa52da615> {
<https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/bc9068b4-00c0-41fd-a1fa-54a3afaa14a4/resource/e8ae6e17-cdad-44d9-a6c0-a6441a1c90b9> a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "vespa_soir_w23p00.ta"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The dataset is present in two formats: in HDF5 (see https://www.hdfgroup.org/solutions/hdf5) \r\nand in VOtables (see https://www.ivoa.net/documents/VOTable/). So the dataset is duplicated.\r\n\r\nThe data in each files are vertical profiles of density for the species which can be CO2, CO, \r\nH2O (H2O_1 for H2O except HDO, H2O_4 for HDO), HF, HCl (HCl_1 for H35Cl, HCl_2 for H37Cl),\r\nSO2 and aerosols (AERO). The files also contains the vertical profile of pressure \"p\" and temperature \"t\".\r\n\r\nThe density \"n_\", logarithm of the density \"log_n_\" and volume mixing ratio \"vmr_\" are provided for \r\nscale heights from 0.1 to 1.0 by step of 0.1. This scale height impacts the smoothing of the profiles.\r\n\r\nThe corresponding uncertainties on the vertical profiles are the variables starting with \"err_\"\r\n\r\nThe data concerning the geometry of the measurements: solar longitude, and local time, \r\nlatitude, longitude corresponding to the profile are also provided in the same files.\r\n\r\nWe encourage you to contact us when you use this dataset or you have a question.\r\nWe kindly request the authors of any communication/publication using \r\nthis dataset to let us know about it and to cite the proper reference paper describing \r\nthis dataset: see list above."@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2024-04-25T11:27:06.458147"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2024-06-20T08:14:08.158485"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/format> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type/GZIP>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#accessURL> <https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/bc9068b4-00c0-41fd-a1fa-54a3afaa14a4>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#downloadURL> <https://data.aeronomie.be/dataset/bc9068b4-00c0-41fd-a1fa-54a3afaa14a4/resource/e8ae6e17-cdad-44d9-a6c0-a6441a1c90b9/download/vespa_soir_w23p00.ta..gz>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/licence/CC_BY_4_0>;
    <http://data.europa.eu/r5r/availability> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/planned-availability/AVAILABLE>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#byteSize> "127921074"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger>
}
